<subSubSection lastPageId="19" lastPageNumber="18" pageId="17" pageNumber="16" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="17.[191,1440,1795,1926]" pageId="17" pageNumber="16">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[192,327,1796,1822]" pageId="17" pageNumber="16">Etymology.</emphasis>
This species is named for Luiz Cordeiro, head of the Forest Protection Sector at the forest company Klabin, and his staff, in Telêmaco Borba, state of 
<collectingRegion box="[755,836,1830,1856]" country="Brazil" name="Parana" pageId="17" pageNumber="16">Paraná</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[848,917,1830,1856]" name="Brazil" pageId="17" pageNumber="16">Brazil</collectingCountry>
, and the person responsible for the establishment of several trapping experiments there over the years, which also resulted in the trapping of this new species.
</paragraph>
